<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bugner Fights Again at 49 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GOLD COAST, Australia (AP) -- Joe Bugner, at 49, won what he said  
was the final fight of 32-year career Sunday when American Levi 
Billups was disqualified for repeated low blows in the ninth round. 
</P>
<P>
	Bugner, a Hungarian who has been living in Australia since the  
early 1980s, twice went the distance with Muhammad Ali, once in a 
world title fight in 1975. 
</P>
<P>
	He won the British, European, Commonwealth, Australian and the  
World Boxing Federation heavyweight titles at various times in his 
career. 
</P>
<P>
	Bugner has announced his retirement three times previously but  
said he is convinced he will stay retired this time. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think after 32 years in the business I've had a very good  
run and I'm very proud to go out on this fight,'' said Bugner. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the bout, Bugner's wife Marlene said she would insist he  
quit for life. 
</P>
<P>
	``If I had my way I would have had him call it quits 22 years  
ago,'' Marlene Bugner said. ``It's terrifying every time he gets 
into the ring. I know he's said he was retiring a few times before 
but this time it's definite.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bugner's record is listed at 69 victories, 13 losses and a draw.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
