<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> United 2, Crew 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Jaime Moreno and Marco Etcheverry hooked  
up on two goals and D.C. goalkeeper Tom Presthus had two saves in a 
two-minute span late in the game as United held off the Crew 2-1 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Columbus (7-5) was held under two goals for the ninth time this  
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Mareno, who scored his fourth and fifth goals, took a pass from  
Etcheverry, sprinted about 40 yards past three defenders and fired 
a shot from about 15 yards past Mark Dougherty to give United a 1-0 
lead in the 34th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 66th minute, Moreno split Michael Clark and Robert  
Warzycha and sent a shot across the box into the left corner past a 
diving Dougherty. 
</P>
<P>
	Etcheverry set up Moreno with a 30-yard pass that rolled  
untouched from near midfield. 
</P>
<P>
	Jeff Cunningham, who didn't play in the first half, scored his  
team-leading fifth goal the 69th minute for Columbus, which went 57 
minutes before testing Presthus. 
</P>
<P>
	United (9-3) played without four starters: forward Roy Lassiter,  
defenders Jeff Agoos and Carlos Llamosa, and midfielder Richie 
Williams. They played for the U.S. national team Sunday in its 1-0 
win over Argentina in RFK Stadium in Washington 
</P>
<P>
	Crew forward Stern John and defender Ansil Elcock missed the  
game to play for Trinidad &AMP; Tobago in the championship game of the 
Copa Caribe tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Columbus missed opportunities to tie in the 75th and 77th  
minutes when Presthus stopped Jeff Farrell from in close and 
blocked Cunningham's drive from the top of the box. 
</P>
<P>
	Matt Kmosko missed a chance to tie the game in the 62nd minute  
when his twisting, right-footed shot sailed just to the left of the 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
	A.J. Wood set up Mareno's first goal with an interception. He  
quickly fed the ball ahead to a cutting Etcheverry. He dribbled a 
few feet before spotting Mareno breaking down the center of the 
field. 
</P>
<P>
	Mareno easily dribbled past Matt Chulis and Mike Lapper, dodged  
a sliding Warzycha, and scored. 
</P>
<P>
	Forward Brian McBride started for Columbus after missing four  
games with a fractured cheekbone. He wore a protective mask. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
