<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Preview Capsule of NBA Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A look at the two teams in the NBA Finals:  
</P>
<P>
 *SAN ANTONIO (37-13 regular season, 11-1 postseason) vs. NEW YORK  
(27-23, 11-4)	
</P>
<P>
	Probable starters: San Antonio -- C David Robinson (15.2 pts, 9.1  
reb, 1.9 stl, 2.08 blk), F Tim Duncan (21.5 pts, 10.4 reb, 2.83 
blk), F Sean Elliott (13.6 pts, 3.6 reb), G Mario Elie (16.4 pts, 
3.3 reb), G Avery Johnson (14.1 pts, 7.5 ast). New York -- C Chris 
Dudley (2.8 pts, 4.8 reb), F Kurt Thomas (5.2 pts, 4.8 reb), F 
Latrell Sprewell (18.5 pts, 4.2 reb), G Allan Houston (17.5 pts), G 
Charlie Ward (4.2 pts, 3.8 ast, 1.5 stl). 
</P>
<P>
	Key reserves: San Antonio -- G Jaren Jackson (20.8 mins, 8.9  
pts), F Jerome Kersey (12.3 mins, 2.8 pts, 2.5 reb), F Malik Rose 
(10.8 mins, 3.3 pts, 2.3 reb), G Steve Kerr (8.8 mins, 2.5 pts). 
New York -- F Marcus Camby (24.9 mins, 10.6 pts, 7.6 reb, 1.87 blk, 
1.4 stl), G Chris Childs (25.9 mins, 4.1 pts, 5.5 ast), F Larry 
Johnson (33.2 mins, 12.7 pts, 4.9 reb). 
</P>
<P>
	Injuries: San Antonio -- G Avery Johnson bruised his knee in the  
conference finals. New York -- C Patrick Ewing is out with a torn 
Achilles tendon. F Larry Johnson is day-to-day with a sprained 
knee. G David Wingate is questionable with a torn quadricep muscle. 
</P>
<P>
	Season series: Did not play.  
</P>
<P>
	Spurs advantages: Size, rebounding, interior defense, health,  
depth. 
</P>
<P>
	San Antonio's tandem of Duncan and Robinson presents serious  
matchup problems for the injury-depleted Knicks, who won't be able 
to put Ewing on Robinson and might not be able to put Johnson on 
anybody if his sprained knee is slow to heal. If Duncan and 
Robinson get into foul trouble, there's plenty of size in reserve 
with Rose, Kersey and Will Perdue. San Antonio's shot blocking 
skills are superior to those of any team the Knicks have faced so 
far. The Spurs are well-rested coming off two straight sweeps. 
</P>
<P>
	Knicks advantages: Speed, athleticism, backcourt scoring,  
intangibles. 
</P>
<P>
	The Knicks found they could thrive in the conference finals when  
they quickened the pace against the old and slow Indiana Pacers. 
The Spurs are a lot quicker, but the Knicks -- especially Sprewell 
and Camby -- can still score and draw fouls in transition. If 
Sprewell and Houston are clicking together, New York's backcourt 
will outscore San Antonio's. As for intangibles, it seems like most 
of the lucky bounces are going their way. They are a confident 
bunch despite their injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	Storyline: Nobody expected the Knicks to be where they are, and  
nobody expects them to have much of a chance against what appears 
to be a superior opponent. 
</P>
<P>
	Prediction: Knicks in 7.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
