<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fugitives Tricked in Prize Offer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) -- The allure of a car and other prizes  
proved enough to win more than 70 curious fugitives something they 
hadn't bargained for -- free lodging in Oakland County's lockup. 
</P>
<P>
	Assorted probation violators and other felons headed out  
Saturday to the Pontiac Silverdome eager for prizes they were told 
awaited them. 
</P>
<P>
	Instead, they got a free trip to jail, courtesy of Pontiac and  
Oakland County authorities, The Oakland Press of Pontiac and The 
Detroit News reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``They're shocked and surprised,'' Lt. Steve Sitar said. ``And  
then we'll get some statements, `Do I still get my TV?''' 
</P>
<P>
	The sting involved mailing out notices weeks ago to some of the  
county's most elusive criminals, informing them that a set of free 
Silverdome tickets, a television and possibly a car were waiting at 
the stadium as part of a random drawing. 
</P>
<P>
	Signs outside the Silverdome said a group called P.O.P.  
Productions was giving away the prizes. The acronym doesn't stand 
for anything, police Capt. Mike Milosic said. 
</P>
<P>
	It means, ``You got popped,'' said Milosic, who wore a special  
red P.O.P. shirt with the Silverdome emblazoned on it. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990613.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-13 22:10:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Mulls Age Limits for Rookies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- NBA commissioner David Stern said he'd like to  
see an age limit for young players coming into the league. 
</P>
<P>
	Stern told The Washington Post in an interview published in  
Monday's editions that with more and more young players leaving 
college early, or skipping it altogether, to turn pro, he'd like to 
work with the players' union to impose a minimum age limit. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have the right to set an age limit in the collective  
bargaining agreement,'' Stern said. ``I believe we can work 
together to come up with something that is legally correct and will 
withstand legal challenge.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The newspaper said that Dan Wasserman, the spokesman for the  
National Basketball Players Association, did not return several 
calls for comment. 
</P>
<P>
	The changes Stern would like to see would not come in time to  
limit the 1999 NBA draft, which will be held in Washington on June 
30. 
</P>
<P>
	According to the Post, the NBA would try to follow the lead of  
the NFL, which has a rule that requires players to have been out of 
high school for three years before they are eligible for the draft. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
