<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tips To Avoiding Computer Virus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	How to avoid the Worm.Explore.Zip virus:  
</P>
<P>
	--The virus is transmitted via e-mail and ruins files on infected  
computers. It appears to come from a friend or acquaintance and 
reads: ``Hi (your name)! I received your e-mail and I shall send 
you a reply ASAP. Till then, take a look at the attached zipped 
docs.'' 
</P>
<P>
	--The message is harmless unless you open the file attached to  
the e-mail. Use caution in opening any attached file, and report 
unusual or suspicious messages to your e-mail provider or system 
administrator. 
</P>
<P>
	--If your computer is infected, repairs are available from  
several online sites. For example, the Symantec AntiVirus Research 
Center has a program to remove the virus. More information is 
available at: http://www.sarc.com/avcenter/kill--ez.html 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
