<HEADLINE> 5 Die As Car Runs Off Bridge in Ky. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HICKMAN, Ky. (AP) -- A car ran off a bridge and landed  
upside-down in a creek, killing the driver and all four of his 
passengers. 
</P>
<P>
	State police were investigating what caused the car driven by  
Maurice Tucker, 56, of Hickman, to crash Saturday, said dispatcher 
Heather Fagan. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials said the car apparently ran up a concrete guide before  
falling at least 15 feet into the creek and landing upside-down in 
5 to 6 feet of water. 
</P>
<P>
	Tucker and three other victims died at the scene; a fifth person  
was taken to Parkway Regional Hospital in Fulton, where he died a 
short time later. 
</P>
<P>
	Hickman is 220 miles southwest of Louisville.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
