<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Small Cruise Ship Runs Aground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JUNEAU, Alaska (AP) -- A small cruise ship ran aground Saturday,  
forcing the evacuation of its 56 passengers and 24 crew members, 
the Coast Guard said. No injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The 157-foot Wilderness Adventurer struck rocks and grounded in  
Dundas Bay, about 50 miles west of Juneau, the Coast Guard said. 
</P>
<P>
	Crew members aboard a U.S. National Park Service aircraft  
reported seeing a fuel sheen near the vessel. The captain told the 
Coast Guard that the ship's hull cracked was taking on water. 
</P>
<P>
	Absorbent booms were deployed around the ship to try to contain  
any spilled fuel. 
</P>
<P>
	The ship is owned and operated by Glacier Bay Tours of Juneau.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
