<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Special Coach Wins Churchill Feature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Special Coach took the lead on the far  
turn and pulled away for a 3 3/4-length victory Sunday over Silver 
Chadra in the $290,500 Jefferson Cup for 3-year-olds at Churchill 
Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Cornelio Velazquez, the 15-1 long shot covered 1 1/8  
miles on the firm turf in 1:49.82 and paid $33, $15 and $8. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver Chadra, ridden by Pat Day, laid just off the lead but  
could not gain on the leader and paid $7.60 and $4.60. Air Rocket, 
the 5-2 favorite ridden by Jerry Bailey, finished another 
three-quarters of a length back in third in the field of 12 and 
paid $3.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Special Coach, owned by the Dixon Raysing Stable and trained by  
William March, won for the fourth time in five career starts on the 
grass and second time in three starts this year. The Florida-bred 
son of Zafarrancho collected $180,110 for Sunday's win to increase 
his lifetime earnings to $248,615. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
