<HEADLINE> Entry Finishes 1-2 at Hollywood Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- French-bred Silic scored a nose victory  
over Ladies Din in the $350,000 Shoemaker Breeder's Cup Mile on the 
turf at Hollywood Park on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The two, racing as an entry, battled through the stretch after  
making their way through traffic in the race for 3-year-olds and 
up. Each carried 124 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Silic, ridden by Corey Nakatani, started slowly and was seventh  
among the eight runners through the first half-mile. Still fifth 
after three-quarters of a mile, he went wide on the turn into the 
stretch and took the lead. He was timed in 1:32.94. 
</P>
<P>
	Ladies Din, ridden by Kent Desormeaux, was fourth much of the  
race until driving to briefly catch the winner in the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	The winning entry paid $10.20, $8 and $5.40. The 3-1 second  
favorite Hawksley Hill, was third, one-half length back, and paid 
$3.20 to show. Poteen finished fourth, a neck behind Hawksley Hill. 
</P>
<P>
	Brave Act, a slight favorite at 11-4, was fifth after staying  
near the middle of the pack throughout. Chullo was sixth followed 
by Fabulous Guy and Lord Smith. Indian Rocket was scratched on 
Saturday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
