<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Angels' Olivares Hits Four Batters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- The Angels' Omar Olivares hit four  
batters with pitches Sunday in Anaheim's game against the Arizona 
Diamondbacks, tying a major league record. 
</P>
<P>
	He became the 19th pitcher to hit four batters in a game, but  
the second Angels' pitcher in three weeks. Anaheim's Steve Sparks 
hit four Tampa Bay batters on May 22. 
</P>
<P>
	Olivares hit Andy Fox in the third inning, Dave Dellucci in the  
fifth, Kelly Stinnett in the sixth and Dellucci again in the 
seventh. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
