<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New England 4, Miami 3, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Johnny Torres and Edwin Gorter each scored  
in the final six minutes of regulation to lead the New England 
Revolution to a 4-3 shootout victory over the Miami Fusion on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	New England tied the game 2-2 on Torres' goal in the 85th  
minute. Miami's Diego Serna scored two minutes later to make it 
3-2, but Gorter scored with 1:51 remaining to send the match into a 
shootout before a crowd of 19,069 at Foxboro Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	The Revolution (6-6) won their third straight and extended  
Miami's winless streak on the road to 11 matches, including eight 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
	In the shootout, Torres, John Harkes and Gorter scored on New  
England's first, second and fourth attempts against Miami 
goalkeeper Jeff Cassar. 
</P>
<P>
	Henry Gutierrez's first attempt for Miami (4-10) bounced off the  
left goalpost. Maurizio Rocha's shot was stopped by New England 
goalkeeper Jeff Causey and a shot by Jeremy Aldrich sailed wide 
left. 
</P>
<P>
	The teams matched first-half goals. Torres put New England ahead  
in the 20th minute, converting a long kick from goalkeeper Walter 
Zenga. Miami countered in the 24th minute when Gutierrez placed a 
23-yard direct kick from the right side over Zenga's right 
shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami outshot New England 14-12 and had a 14-9 edge in corner  
kicks. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyrone Marshall put Miami ahead 2-1 in the 64th minute of the  
match, beating a New England defender for possession of the ball 
inside the penalty box. 
</P>
<P>
	Torres tied the match for New England on a penalty kick after  
Miami defender Arley Palacios took down Revolution forward Jamar 
Beasley with a tackle from behind in the low left corner of the 
penalty box. 
</P>
<P>
	Serna regained the lead for Miami when Gutierrez intercepted  
Zenga's low clearing kick and knocked the ball back into the 
penalty box, where Welton slid the ball left to the Fusion's 
leading scorer. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
